The MHD Wednesday in Prague will accompany you for the first time even with an electronic card
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be written in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the metro, tramway and bus will pick up the first passengers who instead of the paper ticket will have an electronic card in their pocket.
Right now, they can get about 100,000 people who own their own Opencard card.
Passengers can buy the one from 30 and 90 days and annual (which will be valid from the first January 2009) and at the same time have their card recharged in the Infopoint and in the offices of the Company of Transportation and at the metro stop Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letřany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
The coupons can be bought from yesterday on the internet to the page of the Company of Transports www.dppp.cz.
The service took advantage of more than 400 customers before the afternoon.
Those who start using the service via the internet can completely forget the counters in the metro stops where so far they had to make long files for paper tickets.
The coupon is bought via the internet and on the Opencard they reload it on one of the twelve branches of the Municipal Library.
"In these places passengers have at their disposal a desk with trained staff that will help interested parties in buying on the internet and will also record on their card the acquired credit." said project spokesperson Martin Opatrný.
In addition to the libraries it will be possible to load electronic coupons on the Opencards in ATMs and selfservices that are installed at the entrances of the metro.
How are these ATMs?
They are red, resembling the ticket changers and the passengers have already noticed them at the stops of the Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro.
"Now there are five of them all over the city, but by the end of the year there should be eighty," concluded Opatrný.
The coupon will be checked instead of by the driver from the ATM.
The ATM service that will run from tomorrow is very simple.
Just enter the Opencard card and upon payment of the coupon, it will load on.
The electronic cards are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is, in urban lines of trains and buses from 300 to 499, which the inhabitants of the municipalities of Central Bohemia take to reach the capital.
"In the trains added in the integrated transport of Prague there are the controllers equipped with readers of the cards with which they verify the temporal and zonal validity," explained the mode of control of the tickets Filip from the organization Ropid, that it finalizes the times of the collective transport of Prague.
Urban buses have card readers integrated into the driver's box.
During the climb it is therefore necessary not only to show the magnetic card to the driver, but also to place the Opencard at the point determined next to the box.
So the driver checks the validity of the uploaded coupons.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the uploaded coupons, there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this kind of information," added Drápal.
Passengers who take city buses and do not remember, when the validity of the coupon expires, can again go to the self-service ATM, where the coupons are loaded on the card.
Information on the validity of their documents on the screen of the apparatus will be displayed here.
The Germans of the Sudetans wanted a referendum from the USA
The Germans of the Sudetans in 1945 asked to include Šumava in the United States.
This results from the letter deposited in the Scientific Library of South Bohemia.
