Civil rights, however, helped and created space for many other Zora Neale Hurstons - a black writer, actress and artist who surpassed prejudices, as he did, with cheerful self-confidence and lines like: "How can some deny themselves the pleasure of my company!
I just don't understand. "
In 1975, writer Alice Walker began a long journey through Hurston's unmarked grave and began fighting for the resurrection of her reputation.
