Mrs. Boyd makes it easier: "Zora saved Eatonville."
The victory over the highway project helped to change the imagination that the city has of itself.
Those from out of town like Rachelle Munson, a lawyer who started coming to church here in 1993, began to appear in large numbers, and residents began to reevaluate the past.
Eatonville joined the historical public register in 1998.
