The passion for portraits led Bauer to repeat the idea two years ago with "Portraits of veteran athletes" ("Sportartproject").
Although in "Flamenco-People" the concept is different, the photographer admits "I love portraying people, knowing them and being able to penetrate for a moment in their lives, whether this is a long or short moment.
I think the portrait is the hardest kind in photography.
You meet or confront people, characters you sometimes don't even know or who only give you a few minutes to take the picture.
Beyond these circumstances, as a photographer, I always try to put my ideas into practice. "
The collection of portraits of the contemporary flamenco, entitled "Flamenco-people" is set up at the gallery El Fotómata, at 20 Via de la Mata, parallel to Via Alameda de Hercules, and will be open to the public until October 16.
