In the September 17 edition, Le Devoir published a letter from M. Patrick J. Garver, vice-president director of the Canadian mining company Barrick Gold.
Following an Orwellian logic, the latter states that the world's largest advertising company has filed a six million defamation claim against three authors and a small, squatted publishing house with the intention of launching a "transparent public debate."
If it is true that judges are independent and impartial, it is not the truth they judge, especially in the case of a complaint for defamation, but the law.
