Industrial prices continue to rise
National industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
Export sales prices of the industry in July 2008 were 1.1% higher than in the previous year but fell by 3.9%.
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than in the previous month and 3.2% higher than in a year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales compared to the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
The domestic sales prices of the processing sector also rose to a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The biggest increase in prices in August 2008 was in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoes production with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price of plastic and chemical raw materials resulted in a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the products and chemicals sector.
Prices fell in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum in wood processing (0.1%).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry, prices increased by between 0.2% and 0.9%.
In the supply of electricity, gas, steam and water prices increased in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, mainly as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in gas prices made by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared with the domestic sales of the processing industry over 12 months, the largest increases were in the oil processing sector (32.4%).
In the metalworking industry, prices rose by 13.2%, by 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco.
Prices fell in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increases varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
Total prices in the processing industry rose by 10.2% over the past year.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded last year's prices by 18.7%.
In domestic sales between target groups in the sectors, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the consumer goods sectors prices have risen by 0.3%, in the energy and later use sectors prices have not changed compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared with the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy and later use sectors (16.8%).
In the consumer goods sectors, the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales in florins increased in August by 1,1% compared to the previous month, compared in 12 months, by 3,9%.
